description: Majorca is the largest island in the Balearic Islands archipelago in the western Mediterranean Sea.

history.comment: Reimported full way geometry and updated provenance

names.details: Cezīre-i Mayorḳa: It is recorded in the Taḳvīmü’l-büldān that it lies at the far end of the islands under Muslim control. And this island measures forty miles from north to south. Apart from its inhabited city, its well-known fortresses are also firmly established. As for the flowing water (the principal spring) of its capital, it appears with the utmost elegance beneath its huge citadel… [partial translation]
